Kisumu Governor Jack Ranguma has told his main competitor Anyang&rsquo; Nyong&rsquo;o to prepare for defeat.He said there will be no room for manipulating the election &ldquo;as happened during the ODM primaries&rdquo;.Ranguma will run as an independent candidate.Ranguma and Nyong&rsquo;o will face Atieno Atieno of the Jubilee Party. The governor insisted he won during the ODM primaries, but was rigged out.He said his opponents have always spoken of democracy and wondered whether what transpired with the announcement of results of the primaries was part of democracy.&ldquo;It&rsquo;s unfortunate the same person who has been talking about democracy is the one who ran with votes to Thurdibuoro in Nyakach to announce the results. This was shaming the Luo community,&rdquo; Ranguma said.The governor spoke on Wednesday when he visited Nyabondo Boys Boarding Primary School in Nyakach subcounty after a fire razed a dormitory.Ranguma promised he will work with the school administration to reconstruct the dormitory and restore learning.He was accompanied by his running mate Ephraim Kananga, who promised to deliver sufficient votes for their victory. bid.Ranguma dropped Deputy Governor Ruth Odinga and picked Kananga who hails from Nyakach subcounty. Nyong&rsquo;o has also picked Mathew Owili as his running mate from the same area.The governor urged residents to ensure they vote for NASA presidential candidate Raila Odinga for president.&ldquo;We don&rsquo;t have a problem up there. Let&rsquo;s all ensure we vote for Raila, but when we come at the county, vote for Ranguma,&rdquo; he said.